<p>
== Basic API using padrino and mongodb
</p>
<p>
There is 2 objects : User and Post
</p>
<p>
  Following routes are availables :
  <table>
    <tr>
      <td>URL</td>
      <td>REQUEST</td>
      <td>PATH</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>(:posts, :index)</td>
      <td>GET</td>
      <td>/posts</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>(:posts, :search)</td>
      <td>GET</td>
      <td>/search</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>(:posts, :create)</td>
      <td>POST</td>
      <td>/posts</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>(:posts, :show)</td>
      <td>GET</td>
      <td>/posts/:id</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>(:posts, :update)</td>
      <td>PUT</td>
      <td>/posts/:id</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>(:posts, :destroy)</td>
      <td>DELETE</td>
      <td>/posts/:id</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>(:users, :index)</td>
      <td>GET</td>
      <td>/users</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>(:users, :create)</td>
      <td>POST</td>
      <td>/users</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>(:users, :show)</td>
      <td>GET</td>
      <td>/users/:id</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
