      <td>DELETE</td>
      <td>/users/:id</td>
    </tr>
  </table>
    
</p>
<p>
Some examples commands
</p>
<p>
Create a User : curl --data "user[name]=name1&user[age]=22&user[email]=example@example.com" http://api-padrino-mongo.herokuapp.com/users
</p>
<p>
List all Users : http://api-padrino-mongo.herokuapp.com/users
</p>
<p>
Delete a User : curl -i -H "Accept: application/json" -X DELETE hhttp://api-padrino-mongo.herokuapp.com/users/50c7715d35217309ba000028
</p>
<p>
Create a Post for a User : curl -F "post[title]=postTitle1" -F "post[body]=postBody1" -F "post[user_id]=50c71b7c3521730377000001" -F "post[file]=@README.md" http://api-padrino-mongo.herokuapp.com/posts
</p>
<p>
Get the uploaded file : http://api-padrino-mongo.herokuapp.com/system/files/README.md
</p>
<p>
You can search posts on Title and Body attributes by requesting something like : 
http://api-padrino-mongo.herokuapp.com/search?q=keywords</p>

<p>There is a private attribute for User called Age which is only display if your request contains token=s3cr3t for e.g : http://api-padrino-mongo.herokuapp.com/users?token=s3cr3t</p>

